I see - GC is disabled by default! The error "integer representation too long" at offset 0x28 is because the struct type (0x5F) is being rejected. Let me verify:

Looking at `lib/loader/ast/section.cpp:58-59`:
```cpp
if (!Conf.hasProposal(Proposal::GC) && Code != TypeCode::Func) {
    return logNeedProposal(ErrCode::Value::IntegerTooLong, Proposal::GC, ...);
}
```

So without GC, the struct type is rejected. The error is actually from loading the type section - the error says "At AST node: recursive type" and "At AST node: type section". The byte offset 0x0B (where 0x5F is) triggers this.

But wait, the offset in the error says 0x0000000b which IS the struct type byte! So the error is from the type section loading, not the code section. The error is: "integer representation too long" at offset 0x0b. Let me verify by enabling GC:

